The incident, which happened on the rig 100 miles south-east off the Aberdeen coast, occurred at around 9pm on Sunday night. A spokesperson for the Aberdene Coastguard told The Press and Journal: "We were called to assist police at about 9pm following reports of a man who had fallen overboard from an offshore installation. "We had a helicopter as well as lifeboat vessels dispatched. The incident is still ongoing and crews are still out at sea." We'll be bringing you the very latest updates, pictures and video on this breaking news story. For the latest news and breaking news visit: [/news](/news "‌") Stay up to date with all the big headlines, pictures, analysis, opinion and video on the stories that matter to you. Follow our social media accounts here on [facebook.com/DailyExpress](http://facebook.com/DailyExpress "‌") and @daily_express